# ===========================================
# Environment Variables — COPY to .env and fill in real values
# ===========================================
# This file contains NO real secrets — safe to commit to GitHub.
# Create your own .env file (gitignored) with real values.

# 1. DATABASE_URL
#    - Local dev (SQLite):  file:./dev.db
#    - Vercel (Postgres):   postgresql://user:pass@host:5432/db?sslmode=require
#      Get a free Postgres URL from https://neon.tech
DATABASE_URL="file:./dev.db"

# 2. ADMIN_PASSWORD — choose your own password for the admin panel
ADMIN_PASSWORD="your-password-here"

# 3. SESSION_SECRET — any random string (used to sign session cookies)
#    Generate one: openssl rand -hex 32
SESSION_SECRET="generate-a-random-string-here"

# ===========================================
# IMPORTANT: .env.local
# ===========================================
# The platform's startup script resets .env to only DATABASE_URL on every restart.
# To keep your ADMIN_PASSWORD and SESSION_SECRET persistent, put them in .env.local:
#
#   Create .env.local with:
#     ADMIN_PASSWORD=your-password-here
#     SESSION_SECRET=your-random-secret-here
#
# Next.js loads .env.local with HIGHER priority than .env, and the platform
# never touches .env.local — so your secrets survive restarts.
# .env.local is gitignored — never uploaded to GitHub.
